description: Returns a list of telemetry configurations for AWS resources supported by telemetry config in the organization.

parameters.name: AccountIdentifiers
parameters.description: A list of AWS account IDs used to filter the resources to those associated with the specified accounts. (string) ---

parameters.name: ResourceTypes
parameters.description: A list of resource types used to filter resources in the organization. If this parameter is provided, the resources will be returned in the same order used in the request. (string) ---

parameters.name: TelemetryConfigurationState
parameters.description: A key-value pair to filter resources in the organization based on the telemetry type and the state of the telemetry configuration. The key is the telemetry type and the value is the state. (string) --- (string) ---

parameters.name: ResourceTags
parameters.description: A key-value pair to filter resources in the organization based on tags associated with the resource. Fore more information about tags, see What are tags? (string) --- (string) ---

nested_items.name: TelemetryConfigurations
nested_items.description: A list of telemetry configurations for AWS resources supported by telemetry config in the organization.

nested_items.name: AccountIdentifier
nested_items.description: The account ID which contains the resource managed in telemetry configuration. An example of a valid account ID is 012345678901.

nested_items.name: TelemetryConfigurationState
nested_items.description: The configuration state for the resource, for example { Logs: NotApplicable; Metrics: Enabled; Traces: NotApplicable; }.

nested_items.name: ResourceType
nested_items.description: The type of resource, for example AWS::EC2::Instance.

nested_items.name: ResourceIdentifier
nested_items.description: The identifier of the resource, for example i-0b22a22eec53b9321.

nested_items.name: ResourceTags
nested_items.description: Tags associated with the resource, for example { Name: "ExampleInstance", Environment: "Development" }.

nested_items.name: LastUpdateTimeStamp
nested_items.description: The timestamp of the last change to the telemetry configuration for the resource. For example, 1728679196318.

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: The token for the next set of items to return. A previous call provides this token.
